  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently the RLP encoder drops the `Node.DiscPort` field, and during decoding it injects the `TCPPort` into the `DiscPort`: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/develop/p2p/discover/node.go#L125\n\nIt should be a trivial fix (Go side), but I don't know if simply refactoring `rpcNode` has outside effects too, like screwing up the discovery protocol wire format, or only touches the `udp` packet. @fjl Any input on this?\n",
